<item>
            <title>[QPID-3539] NoLocal should occur at the connection level and not the session level (0-10)</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/QPID-3539</link>
                <project id="12310520" key="QPID">Qpid</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;According to the JMS spec the setting of the NoLocal parameter to the method createDurableSubscriber should prevent the delivery of messages produced by the same connection, this is not the behavior in Qpid for 0-10.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This appears to be because NoLocal is done at a session level rather than at connection level.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
